&lt;Newman Industries Plc> said it wasdiscussing the possible merger of its electric motor operationswith Hawker Siddeley Group Plc's &lt;HSID.L> &lt;Brook CromptonParkinson Motors Ltd> unit.    Newman has electric motor operations in the U.K. AndAustralia. The company gave no further details but said afurther statement would be made shortly.    Newman shares eased one penny on the announcement to 43pwhile Hawker was unchanged at 528p, three pence higher on lastnight's close. REUTER&#3;